    "summary": "CrowdStrike exposes the Falcon HTTP API, an Identity Protection GraphQL API, and the self-hosted falcon-mcp package as both a CLI and MCP server; Falcon integrations authenticate with CrowdStrike API client credentials, while HTTP access to a self-hosted MCP server can also be protected by a local x-api-key.",
